{
	"nodes":[
		{"id":"be48baaf458316ad","type":"text","text":"### Shared Extension and code Generator\n- [ ] Fixed Sized arrays are still broken.\n- [ ] Because the object acts like a view, it can be broken easily if the bytes are modified.\n    - [ ] Add an `is_valid()` function.\n    - [ ] can I mark the bytes as read only?\n- [x] reserving 'start' is super annoying, make it something more unique so others can use the word.\n- [x] reduce surface area of API by using Enum's to indicate which type to serialise as.\n- [ ] I want a create from dict which picks up the fields from the dictionary to populate the flatbuffer\n- [ ] I don't like that test structs are not created simply, new can allocate the buffer, but I want to pass it values in the creation function. so some static overloads may be desirable.","x":-1200,"y":1900,"width":1160,"height":300},
		{"id":"53e5b10bfb42cd3f","type":"text","text":"### General\n- [ ] re-base off godot-cpp-template\n- [ ] add CI/CD\n- [ ] implement flexbuffers\n- [ ] Because the script derivations of the FlatBuffer type inherit from FlatBuffer Object, is it faster to created the Object in C++ when fetching the buffer, can we then take advantage of view like objects for the memory?\n- [ ] Can I mush some of the function calls to fetch data more directly, rather than calculating things in gdscript?","x":-1200,"y":920,"width":1160,"height":220},
		{"id":"140f6eab3b2748c6","type":"text","text":"### Editing Schema Files\n- Godot.Editor.FileSystemDock\n    - [x] (folder)RightClick->New FLatbuffer Schema\n    - [x] .fbs file recognition\n    - [x] icon for .fbs files\n    - [ ] tooltip for .fbs files\n    - [ ] drag-and-drop from filesystem dock\n    - [ ] ctrl+click on identifier switches to the source file.","x":-1200,"y":20,"width":1160,"height":260},
		{"id":"7726037d7d4c004f","type":"text","text":"### Generating GDScript from Schema\n- [ ] Reload script in editor after re-generation\n    - [ ] Do more testing with `{gd} EditorFilesystem.reimport_files()`\n- [ ] Make failed compile popup\n- [ ] Notify user if creation date of the generated script is earlier than the fbs file, or the plugin so they can regenerate it. \n- **`{gd} Godot.ProjectSettings`**\n    - [x] Path to flatc compiler\n    - [x] Generator flag Pre-sets\n    - [ ] Add an option to the settings to auto generate after a fbs file is changed.\n- **`{gd} Godot.CodeEdit`**\n    - [ ] `{gd} sidebar.right-click` -> Generate GDScript\n- **`{gd} Godot.Editor.FileSystemDock`**\n    - [x] (.fbs)RightClick->Generate GDScript\n- `{gd} FlatbuffersGeneratorOpts`\n    - [ ] Add a function to convert a schema path to a generated file path based on the settings\n    - [ ] Add a way to get a fallback option rather than nothing from certain properties","x":-1200,"y":300,"width":1160,"height":480},
		{"id":"b01ef1a392611591","type":"text","text":"### Generating Schema from Objects\n- [ ] Generate Schema from Godot.Object @Exports\n- [ ] I saw someone using a struct visualiser, makes me want to build one for this.","x":-1200,"y":-140,"width":1160,"height":140},
		{"id":"e7ba42bbc6a92030","type":"text","text":"### General\n- [ ] abstract the parser so it can be run on arbitrary text blocks unrelated to the code editor","x":-1200,"y":-280,"width":1160,"height":120},
		{"id":"ec986fb735c5bc92","type":"text","text":"#### Syntax Highlighting\n- [ ] Check names for collision\n- [x] Parse includes for names\n- [ ] Keep track of field names and highlight duplicates\n- [ ] ANNOYING: Parsing runs on every keypress, printing errors each time until correctness is achieved\n- [ ] Add filename to debug print\n- [ ] warn on use of namespace\n- [ ] highlighter shouldn't complain so much on whitespace.\n- `{gd} Godot.ProjectSettings`\n    - [x] Colours\n    - [x] Log/Reporting Levels\n    - [ ] Feature Flags","x":300,"y":-220,"width":562,"height":400},
		{"id":"f3e851224d39fa71","type":"text","text":"#### ToolTips\n- [ ] Figure out how to highlight/tooltip an error or hint.","x":300,"y":200,"width":565,"height":180},
		{"id":"a9086b20bfaf29ad","type":"text","text":"## Godot.Flatbuffers Addon","x":-1980,"y":120,"width":434,"height":60},
		{"id":"c5bcb0c17107b603","type":"text","text":"#### Benchmarking\n- [x] Copy strategy from flatbuffers project\n- [x] Compare against built-in solution.\n- Scenarios\n    - [x] Update from buffer\n    - [ ] Create from buffer\n    - [x] encode and store as buffer\n    - [x] load from decode from buffer\n- Methods\n    - [x] Godot Built-In with GDScript\n    - [ ] Godot Built-In with GDExtension\n    - [x] Flatbuffers with GDScript\n    - [ ] Flatbuffers with GDExtension\n    - [x] Godot Dict - actually really fast.\n- Investigate other languages?\n    - [ ] Rust\n    - [ ] C#\n- Investigate Alternative Methods\n    - [ ] Dictionary\n    - [ ] Custom Objects\n- [x] record buffer size.\n- Variations\n    - [ ] number of fields in dict/table/object\n    - [ ] number of sub dict/table/object in array","x":-1220,"y":-1360,"width":1160,"height":640},
		{"id":"c485e526da3a734b","type":"text","text":"## Development Project","x":-1960,"y":-1000,"width":434,"height":60},
		{"id":"4f690680af7b8e91","type":"text","text":"#### Documentation\n- [ ] Explain Object API","x":-1220,"y":-700,"width":1160,"height":100},
		{"id":"ac486d9519a6928b","type":"text","text":"#### Brainstorming\n- [ ] Due to the nature of how Godot's properties work in GDExtension, I wonder if I can create a class like object in C++ that fetches its properties directly from compiled C++ flatbuffer.","x":-1220,"y":-580,"width":1154,"height":140},
		{"id":"c420fc8f3434bee3","type":"text","text":"## Flatbuffers Compiler","x":-2000,"y":2520,"width":393,"height":60},
		{"id":"0654f9241e433dd6","type":"text","text":"## Godot.Flatbuffers Extension","x":-2040,"y":1480,"width":500,"height":60},
		{"id":"98bff579e01ec478","type":"text","text":"#### Object > FlatBuffer\n- [ ] When accessing nested objects, a new object is created look into sharing memory.\n- [ ] Would be nice to have a reset( data, start ) function\n","x":-1200,"y":1160,"width":1160,"height":120},
		{"id":"69f72ec158e619e4","type":"text","text":"#### Object > FlatBufferBuilder\n- [ ] Sanity check on builder.finish(offset), where offset should exist within the buffer itself.\n- [ ] Create* functions need to be able to take the object, not the offset, i.e. string instead of int where appropriate","x":-1200,"y":1300,"width":1160,"height":140},
		{"id":"d55bdf307e17fb00","type":"text","text":"#### Object > FlatBufferVerifier\n- [x] VerifyTableStart\n- [ ] VerifyField\n- [ ] VerifyFieldRequired\n- [ ] VerifyOffset\n- [ ] VerifyOffsetRequired\n- [ ] VerifyOffset64\n- [ ] VerifyOffset64Required\n- [ ] VerifyStringWithDefault\n- [ ] VerifyVectorWithDefault\n- [ ] VerifyVector64WithDefault","x":-1200,"y":1460,"width":1160,"height":320},
		{"id":"02a6097777384eb4","type":"text","text":"#### FlatBufferVerifier\n> [!missing] requires the extension to have support first.","x":-1200,"y":3020,"width":1160,"height":120},
		{"id":"b8d3ed21fa07214a","type":"text","text":"#### FlatBuffer\n- [x] it used to be the case that the decode of the starting point would happen automatically\n        ~~but something was broken about it and i removed it, now its a real inconvenient to always have to~~\n        ~~pass a decoded start value all the time. I think if the start value is something like 0, then we can decode that location automatically for the real start.~~\n- [ ] custom structs need their memory assigned if they are constructed without arguments.\n- [x] Keep VT_* values for deprecated fields.\n- [x] try a `{gd} enum vtable` with no name, or change its name to `{gd} enum _fb_vtable`\n- [x] remove duplicate size function for vectors of unions","x":-1200,"y":3160,"width":1160,"height":320},
		{"id":"f4628c33a19060c9","type":"text","text":"#### FlatBufferBuilder\n- [ ] add_* function arguments need to be named with \\_offset if they expect an offset instead of a value.\n- [x] boolean value is misrepresented as an int in the create_* functions\n- [x] generated bool accessor is also int\n- [ ] creating a struct as raw bytes right now is separate to the builder buffer. I need to consolidate that.\n    - [ ] can I hand the buffer inside the builder to a struct? would that clobber things?\n- [ ] Provide static builders so that we don't need to allocate an object for each build.\n    - [ ] Requires `_init` function to handle a null value\n    - [ ] naming so far is `_sfbb_{TABLE_NAME}`\n- [ ] Provide alternate constructor for structs that takes a buffer and a start position so that it can be constructed in place.","x":-1200,"y":2680,"width":1160,"height":320},
		{"id":"185f56311febd149","type":"text","text":"### General\n- [x] Add Document Comments for generated code\n- [x] make requiring a root_type optional\n- [x] investigate the use of using the `object._iter*` functions\n    - I haven't thought of a valid use case that would not be purely adding features.\n- [ ] Include file location is a bit broken, it appends the current schema location to the front always. rather than include as is. I think it needs an overhaul\n- [ ] ?custom attribute for `{gd} class_name`?\n- [ ] struct docstring could use some elaboration","x":-1200,"y":2380,"width":1160,"height":280},
		{"id":"ab1ddd21c38a425f","type":"text","text":"#### Testing\n- [ ] Perform testing in CI/CD\n- [ ] Test FlexBuffer Code\n- [ ] Flesh out testing by category\n    - [ ] Schema Parsing\n    - [ ] Code Generation\n    - [ ] Encoding\n    - [ ] Verification\n    - [ ] Decoding\n    - [ ] Using\n- [x] Copy all of the testing cases from the flatbuffers project into a separate folder\n- [ ] Investigate this further: [Cannot resolve `{gd} class_name` in dynamic GDScript](https://github.com/godotengine/godot/issues/98985)","x":-1220,"y":-1720,"width":1160,"height":340}
	],
